<P>
   &UR; THE RETURN OF A DIMINISHED GENERAL PINOCHET &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   As the news came through in the middle of the Santiago night
that Britain was dropping extradition proceedings, and that General
Augusto Pinochet was finally going home, a small group of his
supporters staged a celebration. It may very well be his only
welcome-home reception. During his detention, most Chileans quickly
became bored and baffled by the legal intricacies of the case, and
lapsed into indifference. Chileans discovered that life without
General Pinochet was not only possible, but preferable. &QL;
</P>
