<P>
   NY-WOMEN'S-VOTE (New York) _ Sen. John McCain and Texas Gov.
George W. Bush battle for the women's vote in Tuesday's Republican
presidential primary in New York. McCain defends his record on
federal spending for breast cancer research and touts his plan for
tobacco regulation that would have financed more such research.
Bush visits a cancer research center on Long Island, where breast
cancer rates are among the highest in the nation. By STEWART M.
POWELL and DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
