Tuesday is a crucial test for Texas Gov. George W. Bush, not only
in his battle against Sen. John McCain for the Republican
nomination, but also in his effort to show that he can attract the
Latino vote, which has traditionally gone Democratic. We look at
how Bush is wooing Hispanic communities. By DAN FREEDMAN.
