<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-03 14:41 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5745 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e BC-TV-SOAPS-ADRIENNE-SID     03-03 0165
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-SOAPS-ADRIENNE-SIDE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FRANTZ IN THE SOAP SPOTLIGHT
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Adrienne Frantz, who plays bad girl Amber Moore on ``The Bold
and the Beautiful,'' is one of four soap opera actresses in
contention for Outstanding Younger Lead Actress in the upcoming
Soap Opera Digest Awards.
</P>
<P>
   The awards, voted on by readers of Soap Opera Digest magazine,
are the soap opera equivalent of television and film's People's
Choice Awards.
</P>
<P>
   Frantz, who will also be a presenter on the awards show, is in
contention with Kelly Ripa, who plays Hayley Vaughn on ``All My
Children,'' Alison Sweeney, who portrays Sami Brady on ``Days of
Our Lives,'' and Maura West, who plays Carly Tenney on ``As the
World Turns.''
</P>
<P>
   NBC will broadcast the Soap Opera Digest Awards from 9 to 11
p.m. Friday from the Hollywood Palladium. ``The Bold and the
Beautiful'' airs weekdays at 12:30 p.m. on CBS. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-03-00 1441EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000303.0110 </DOCNO>
