<P>
   SONG-SOPRANOS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Woke Up This Morning,'' the theme song for ``The
Sopranos,'' is one of the best things about the critically
acclaimed HBO series. But does anyone know who sings it? Well, it's
a British group A3, which means Alabama 3, if that makes sense,
especially since there are more than three band members. The song
isn't even new, having been released to little fanfare a while
back. But David chase, the show's creator, heard it one morning and
liked it so much, he made it ``The soprano's'' theme. Now, the song
is getting a second life and being played on radio stations. By
ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LABBE-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Preston King returned to the United States last week
for the first time in 39 years. His arrival, made possible by a
pardon issued by President Clinton, was trumpeted as some kind of a
heroic triumph over a racist wrong done lo, those many years ago.
Too bad the draft dodger didn't stick around long enough to visit
the Korean War memorial in Washington, or walk by The Wall, where
the names of more than 58,000 of this nation's true heroes are
inscribed _ none of them beginning with the word ``Mister.'' By
J.R. LABBE. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Will Rick Rockwell and Darva Conger ever go away?
Shouldn't the clock have run out on their 15 minutes of fame about
two weeks ago? By BILL THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
