<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-03 18:33 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5962 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u v BC-SPOT/FEATURE-BUDGET-B     03-03 0411
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT/FEATURE-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
 
For Release SaturdayDAY AMs, March 4, 2000  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Roy Greene  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PINOCHET-RETURN (Santiago) _ Declared unfit to stand trial in
Europe, former dictator Augusto Pinochet projects strength in a
triumphant homecoming, lifting himself out of a wheelchair and
walking steadily across an airport tarmac to the cheers of adoring
supporters. By Richard Chacon. 1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CHECHNYA-REFUGEES (Sleptsovskaya) _ Chechnya's war-ruined
villages provide little shelter, no food, no work, and no
amenities. But refugees are going back, under great peril, because
they have nowhere else to go. By David Filipov. 1,200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-REPUBLICANS (New York) _ After 48 hours of being
pounded by ads that criticized John McCain for proposing to cut
breast cancer research funding, the Arizona senator's campaign
lashes out at George W. Bush for exploiting the fears of cancer
patients and their families. By John Farrell and Anne Kornblut.
1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANCER-MARROW (Boston) _ A new study says bone marrow
transplants are ineffective when breast cancer has spread to other
organs. By Richard Saltus. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ANIMALS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Tips on dealing with a menacing dog,
