<P>
   DEUTSCHE-TELEKOM (London) _ Looking at Deutsche Telekom's
ambitions. The company has been thwarted before in its efforts to
expand beyond its home market and is clearly eager to make a big
acquisition, most likely in the United States. Toward that end,
Deutsche Telekom has talked to 10 companies in the United States
and abroad, including Qwest Communications and Global Crossing. But
the company faces a number of obstacles to a deal in the United
States. By Andrew Ross Sorkin.
</P>
