<P>
   WASHINGTON WATCH VOTE CHART Questions regarding this
transmission should be directed to 202-628-3100, ext. 227.
WASHINGTON, March 3 -- The following chart shows how senators and
representatives voted on key bills and amendments within the last
week. A ``Y'' means the member voted for the measure; an ``N''
means the member voted against the measure; a ``?'' means the
member did not vote; and a ``P'' means the member voted
``present.''
</P>
<P>
   SENATE VOTES:
</P>
<P>
   1) BILL NUMBER: EDUCATION
</P>
<P>
   The Senate on Thursday approved, 61 to 37, a bill that would
allow families to set up annual tax-free education savings accounts
of up to $2,000 per child for private and public school expenses.
The bill, which would raise the legal limit on the annual savings
account from $500 to $2,000, would also allow married couples with
annual incomes of up to $220,000 to participate. Supporters said
the bill will give states, local school systems and parents more
leeway on how to spend federal education dollars. Opponents,
including President Clinton, said public schools need more federal
funding and would suffer if students attend private schools as a
result of the tax-credit. A ``yes'' vote favors the bill.
</P>
<P>
   VOTE : 1
</P>
