</P>
<P>
   HOUSE VOTES:
</P>
<P>
   1) BILL NUMBER: CAP
</P>
<P>
   The House, in a rare display of unanimity Wednesday, approved a
measure 422 to 0, that will allow people over the age of 65 to keep
their Social Security payments and continue working no matter how
much money they earn. Supporters, including President Clinton, said
elderly Americans are living longer, healthier lives and are needed
in the workforce. A ``yes'' vote favors the measure.
</P>
