A6188 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u k BC-EDITORIAL-NAZI-BOS &LR;      03-03 0380
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDITORIAL-NAZI-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EICHMANN'S ADMISSIONS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For release Sunday, March 5, 2000)  (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Because free and unconstrained historical inquiry is the best
antidote to distortions and falsifications of the past, future
generations will benefit from Israel's release this week of Adolf
Eichmann's self-serving 1,200-page handwritten memoir of his role
in the Third Reich's bureaucratic annihilation of 6 million Jews.
</P>
<P>
   At a time when neo-Nazis in Europe and North America are
attempting to deny the Holocaust and the Syrian regime of Hafez
Assad is pretending the genocide supervised by Eichmann was a
Zionist ``myth,'' it should be evident that there will always be a
need to have as much documentation as possible about what
Eichmann's manuscript calls ``the greatest crime committed in the
history of humanity.''
</P>
<P>
   It is unfortunate, however, that the immediate reason for
Israel's release of Eichmann's prison writings is a need to assist
in the defense of Emory University professor Deborah Lipstadt, who
has been sued for libel in a British court by David Irving. The
notorious Irving alleges that Lipstadt defamed him in her book
``Denying the Holocaust: The Growing Assault on Truth and Memory.''
</P>
<P>
   Irving, who has tried to claim that Hitler never knew the full
truth of what was being done in the death camps, claims that he
cannot be called a Holocaust denier merely because he questions the
number of Jews murdered and denies that the Nazi death machine
administered by Eichmann included the use of gas chambers.
</P>
<P>
   A good cause will be served if Eichmann's prison writings help
disprove Irving's charge of libel. Despite their transparent and
contemptible pretense that he was merely a ``cog in the giant wheel
of the Third Reich,'' Eichmann's memoirs offer a detailed
perpetrator's account of what he calls genocide _ ``Volkermord.''
</P>
<P>
   Nevertheless, the pursuit of historical truth does not belong in
a courtroom. It should not be up to even the most fair-minded judge
or jury to decide if a historian has lied about the past or been
defamed by another historian. Not even when the subject in dispute
is the ultimate evil of the genocide that Hitler's heirs wish to
deny.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-03-00 2018EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
