<P>
   CRASH-DEACTIVATION (Los Angeles) _ As the LAPD grapples with the
corruption scandal from the Rampard CRASH unit, Police Chief
Bernard Parks issued a directive Friday announcing that all CRASH
units citywide will be de-activated effective a week from Sunday.
This will be the beginning of a 30-day reorganization involving
more than a mere name change, and will include new priorites, Parks
said. By Rick Orlov and Lisa Van Proyen. (Will run in the ``a''
national and ``n'' state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BELMONT-REVIVAL (Los Angeles) _ Under an intensive lobbying
effort to bring the Belmont Learning Center back from the dead, the
Los Angeles City Council is seeking to pressure the Board of
Education by requiring the school district to justify any school
built in the Belmont cluster. Councilman Joel Wachs is warning the
city about an unholy alliance attempting to revive the
scandal-plagued project. By Rick Orlov and Gret Gittrich. (Will run
in the ``a'' national and ``n'' state news files.)
</P>
