<SLUG> BC-BIZ-DIARY-$ADV05-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHORT ITEM ON BUSINESS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, MARCH 5) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   So, Tune In Next Time For `A Cool Sales Idea,' or `Frozen
Chocolate Moose' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mars Inc., the candy giant, is giving ``The Adventures of Rocky
and Bullwinkle,'' the coming summer film, a chilly reception _
literally.
</P>
<P>
   Mars is using the cartoon duo's imaginary home, Frostbite Falls,
Minn., in a tie-in promotion to get children and adults to enjoy
frozen Milky Way, Snickers, Twix and Three Musketeers bars.
</P>
<P>
   The candy maker is one of seven promotional partners linked to
the movie, which will mix live action with animation a la ``Who
Framed Roger Rabbit.'' Universal Studios has also licensed more
than 60 Rocky and Bullwinkle products, from gifts to home
furnishings.
</P>
<P>
   The film updates Jay Ward's slyly subversive 1960s cartoon
series, whose Cold War satire and groaning puns made it as popular
with adults as with children. This time, live actors will play the
heavies: Jason Alexander and Rene Russo as Boris and Natasha, the
hapless Pottsylvanian spies, and Robert De Niro as their Fearless
Leader.
</P>
<P>
   The attraction for Mars, besides the nostalgia value and the
obvious fit with Frostbite Falls, was the timing _ candy sales
usually dip in the warm weather of summer, when the promotion will
run, said Michelle Weese, a Mars spokeswoman. ``We just thought it
would be a cool thing to be associated with,'' she said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _Patricia Winters Lauro
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
