be approved this week in the Senate. Many conservative Republicans
oppose Richard Paez's nomination to the U.S. 9th Circuit Court of
Appeals because they say he is too liberal. But defenders of Paez,
a U.S. District Court judge in Los Angeles, deny that. By MARK
HELM. (Filed Friday.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ABANDONED-RAILROAD (Presidio, Texas) _ For nearly a century, the
South Orient railroad has spurred hope of trade between the United
States and Mexico, and has delivered decades of disappointment. Now
Texas officials say they are in a race against time to save the
little-known railroad that crosses the Rio Grande on a wooden
trestle. While the North American Free Trade Agreement has turned
the other railroad tracks that connect the two countries into busy
routes, the San Angelo-to-Presidio line has sprouted weeds. By
RUSSELL GOLD. (Filed Friday.)
</P>
