who would be president have been called such things as liars,
cheats, cowards and phonies. But such vitriol is nothing new. It is
part of a tradition that began in 1796 with the first presidential
clash between Thomas Jefferson and John Adams. By ROBERT E.
THOMPSON. (Filed Thursday.)
</P>
