<HEADLINE>
AYALA GOES AT IT AGAIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MICHAEL ROSENTHAL  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS _ Paulie Ayala, perhaps the least-known fighter ever
named The Ring magazine's Fighter of the Year, defends his WBA
bantamweight title against Johnny Bredahl of Denmark tonight at
Mandalay Bay Events Center.
</P>
<P>
   Ayala (29-1, with 12 knockouts) gave one of boxing's most
impressive performances last June when he narrowly outpointed
previously unbeaten and favored Johnny Tapia here.
</P>
<P>
   The Fort Worth, Tex., resident outpointed Sahoiu Sithchai Condo
in October in his first title defense.
</P>
<P>
   The light-punching Bredahl (45-1, 23 KOs) is the European
Champion but not given a good chance of beating Ayala, a slick
boxer and one of the toughest guys around.
</P>
<P>
   An 10-round undercard matchup of junior middleweight contenders
Yory Boy Campas (74-3, 63 KOs) and Oba Carr (49-3-1, 29 KOs) is
much more intriguing.
</P>
<P>
   Also on the pay-per-view card: WBA super bantamweight champ
Nestor Garza (37-1, 29 KOs) defends against Bones Adams (38-3-3, 18
KOs); super bantamweight contender Danny Romero (37-3-1, 32 KOs)
faces Adarryl Johnson(11-3-2, six KOs) in a 10-round bout; and Eric
``Butterbean'' Esch (52-1-2, 39 KOs) takes on George Linberger
(18-4-1, 17 KOs) in a four-round heavyweight matchup.
</P>
</TEXT>
