   (NYT32) NEW YORK -- March 3, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 5 --
ABOUT-CARS-MERCEDES -- In the current feeding frenzy, the
definition of sport utility has hopelessly moved beyond the
original notion of a truck with a covered bed and four-wheel-drive
to manage the hunting trail. It now covers virtually anything that
has big, knobby tires and a hefty dose of attitude. Still, there
must be limits, and the Mercedes-Benz ML55 AMG might be somewhere
just beyond them. (The New York Times)
