MARKET-WEALTH-SPEND -- David Brancaccio, host of the public radio
program ``Marketplace,'' has just written a book called
``Squandering Aimlessly,'' an account of what people around the
country do, or could do, with a chunk of extra money. Since this
was publication day, and Simon &AMP; Schuster owed him $25,000, he
wanted his check, and he wanted to imagine what he could do with
that sum - on the spot. ``Let's see,'' he said, pulling out a
calculator. ``Minus the agent's commission, that's $21,250.''
(Chester Higgins Jr./The New York Times) LITE
