<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- March 3, 2000 -- NOISE-THEATER-REVIEW-2 --
Darkness is the earth and oxygen of ``The Noise of Time,'' the
exquisitely realized elegy of a performance piece created by the
Theatre de Complicite. Antonio Gil Martinez, one of the show's four
nonmusical performers, shared the stage with a cello during the
performance. (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
