<P>
   (NYT24) PARIS -- March 3, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 5 --
RENZO-PIANO-ARCH-B&AMP;W -- Even now, at 62, Renzo Piano seemed amazed
that France had allowed two young foreigners - he was 33 and his
British partner, Richard Rogers, was 37 - to challenge the sober
18th-century stone facades of eastern Paris with their immense
metallic design for the Georges Pompidou Center there. ``President
Pompidou was very courageous, that's for sure,'' said Piano, left,
shown with Rogers during construction of the center. (Richard
Rogers Partnership/The New York Times)
