<P>
   (NYT23) ISTANBUL, Turkey -- March 3, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN.,
MARCH 5 -- TURKEY-ART -- An exhibition called ``Palace of Gold and
Light: Treasures From the Topkapi, Istanbul'' opened Wednesday at
the Corcoran Gallery of Art in Washington, and is scheduled to
travel to museums across America. Built in the 15th century, the
Topkapi Palace stands high atop a bluff with panoramic views of
Asia and Europe. The rooftops of the building's harem are shown,
looking north toward the Bosporus. (Palace Arts Foundation/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- March 3, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 5 --
DYLAN-MUSIC -- John Corigliano, at his Manhattan apartment last
month, has created ``Mr. Tambourine Man: Seven Songs of Bob
Dylan,'' a 35-minute song cycle based on some of Dylan's lyrics.
``He might not like what I've done,'' says Corigliano, 62. ``But if
the poetry is good, it can stand it, just as a poem by Goethe can
stand different settings by Schumann, Brahms or Wolf. And I think
it is good, otherwise I wouldn't have set it.'' (Richard Perry/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
