DALLAS-SYMPHONY-B&AMP;W -- Tell a New Yorker that the symphony
orchestra in Dallas is 100 years old, and the reaction will
probably be surprise. The Dallas Symphony Orchestra would like to
change that, despite a history that has followed a rollercoaster
track of highs and lows. Its first concert took place in Turner
Hall in Dallas in 1900. (Dallas Symphony Orchestra/The New York
Times)
