<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Game Report: Braves 7, Royals 3
 &HT;    By Carroll Rogers
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   THE GOOD:
</P>
<P>
   Andres Galarraga continued his recovery from lymphoma with two
hits to drive in a pair of runs. George Lombard, who hit 11 home
runs in the Arizona Fall League to tie the league record, continued
his power surge with a three-run shot. He took Chris Fussell deep
off a sign over the wall in left-center field. Brian Jordan
continued his hot start after going 2-for-2 with a homer against
Georgia on Thursday. Jordan singled and then reached second on an
error off left fielder Johnny Damon on a ball he launched to deep
left field.
</P>
<P>
   THE BAD:
</P>
<P>
   Trenidad Hubbard got picked off second base by Jay Witasick,
spoiling his leadoff hit. Hubbard had advanced into scoring
position on a good bunt by Kevin Millwood. ... With the bases
loaded in the fifth inning, Mark DeRosa grounded into a 6-4-3
double play to end the inning. ... The Royals committed three
errors, contributing to four Brave runs.
</P>
<P>
   THIS AND THAT:
</P>
<P>
   Witasick put Millwood on his back with an eye-level pitch in his
first at bat of the spring. But Millwood was able to come back on
the next pitch and lay down the bunt.
</P>
<P>
   UPCOMING:
</P>
<P>
   Today _ Braves vs. Devil Rays at St. Petersburg, 1:05 p.m. RHP
Greg Maddux, RHP Richard Dishman, RHP Jason Marquis, RHP Rafael
Medina, RHP David Cortes vs. RHP Ryan Rupe, RHP Roberto Hernandez,
RHP Jeff Sparks, RHP Mickey Callaway. Sunday _ Braves vs. Devil
Rays at Disney, 1:05 p.m. RHP John Smoltz, RHP Everett Stull, LHP
Damian Moss, LHP Mike Remlinger, RHP Kevin McGlinchy vs. RHP Dan
Wheeler, RHP Marc Valdes, RHP Chris Reitsma, RHP Travis Harper, RHP
Rick White.
</P>
